    Example Analysis

    Extract lmList Object Data

    getData.lmList.Rd

    If present in the calling sequence used to produce object, the data frame used to fit the model is obtained.

    Usage

    # S3 method for lmList
getData(object)

    Arguments

    object

    an object inheriting from class lmList, representing a list of lm objects with a common model.

    Value

    if a data argument is present in the calling sequence that produced object, the corresponding data frame (with

    na.action and subset applied to it, if also present in the call that produced object) is returned; else, NULL is returned.

    Author

    José Pinheiro and Douglas Bates bates@stat.wisc.edu

    See also

    lmList, getData

    Examples

    fm1 <- lmList(distance ~ age | Subject, Orthodont)
getData(fm1)
